# Motorsport APIPortfolio-ready backend API built with Django and Django REST Framework.## What this project demonstrates- Relational data modeling (`Team` -> `Driver`)- REST API design with versioned routes (`/api/v1/`)- JWT authentication for protected write operations- Public read / admin-only write permissions- Filtering, pagination, standings endpoint- OpenAPI docs with Swagger and ReDoc- Automated API tests## Tech stack- Python 3.12+- Django- Django REST Framework- drf-spectacular- djangorestframework-simplejwt- SQLite (development)## API endpoints (v1)- `GET /api/v1/drivers/`- `GET /api/v1/drivers/standings/`- `GET /api/v1/drivers/by-team/<team_id>/`- `GET /api/v1/teams/`- `GET /api/v1/teams/<id>/`- `GET /api/v1/stats/`- `POST /api/v1/auth/token/`- `POST /api/v1/auth/token/refresh/`Filtering examples:- `GET /api/v1/drivers/?team=1`- `GET /api/v1/drivers/?country=italy`- `GET /api/v1/drivers/?min_points=200`- `GET /api/v1/teams/?country=uk`Docs:- Swagger: `/api/docs/`- ReDoc: `/api/redoc/`- OpenAPI schema: `/api/schema/`## Quick start```bashpython -m venv .venv.venv\Scripts\activatepip install -r requirements.txtpython manage.py migratepython manage.py createsuperuserpython manage.py seed_motorsportpython manage.py runserver```## Environment variablesCopy `.env.example` and set values in your shell:- `DJANGO_SECRET_KEY`- `DJANGO_DEBUG`- `DJANGO_ALLOWED_HOSTS`## Run tests```bashpython manage.py test```## Security model- Read endpoints are public.- Write endpoints (`POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE`) require admin user.- JWT tokens are used for API authentication.## Portfolio talking points- Designed API contract and versioning from day 1.- Added domain-specific endpoints (`standings`, `by-team`, `stats`).- Enforced role-based access policy.- Built test coverage for critical flows.